      <h1 class="content-hero-title">Mescaline: Peyote, San Pedro &amp; Ethical Engagement</h1>
      <p class="content-hero-subtitle">Mescaline is a naturally occurring phenethylamine found primarily in peyote (<em>Lophophora williamsii</em>) and San Pedro cactus (<em>Echinopsis pachanoi</em>). It is one of the oldest known psychedelic substances &mdash; used ceremonially by Indigenous peoples of the Americas for thousands of years. This guide covers mescaline&rsquo;s pharmacology, effects, the critical ethical dimensions of non-Indigenous engagement, and harm reduction.</p>
    </div>

